  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "Driver Dan's Story Train (Arabic: كابتن كريم وقطار الحكايات, Captain Karim Qitar Al Hekayat (Captain Karim and the Story Train)) is a children's television series created and designed by Rebecca Elgar and is a co-production between Two Four 54 in the United Arab Emirates and 3Line Media in the United Kingdom. It marked the first CGI animated/live-action property to be produced in both English and Arabic, which each have its own separate versions of the program.\nThe series debuted on CBeebies and Al Jazeera Children's Channel on 9 January 2010. It was shown by Sprout, CBeebies, and ABC2.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
